org.apache.river.api.io

Class AtomicException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.apache.river.api.io.AtomicException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LeaseException, LeaseUnmarshalException, LookupUnmarshalException, ThrowThis, TransactionException, UnusableEntriesException

    public abstract class AtomicException
extends Exception
    Although most Throwable classes are serialized over AtomicMarshalOutputStream, only Throwable's fields are transferred. If an Exception needs to serialize additional state, then AtomicException provides an abstract superclass, that serializes Throwable's fields for convenience.
    Author:
    peter
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
